<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56a63c77-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s943"><num value="943">§ 943.</num><heading> Arms and ammunition; immunity from taxation</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No tax on the sale or transfer of firearms, pistols, revolvers, shells, or cartridges may be imposed on such articles when bought with funds appropriated for the Coast Guard.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id56a63c78-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/87/526/s1/6">Pub. L. 87–526, § 1(6)</ref>, <date date="1962-07-10">July 10, 1962</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/76/142">76 Stat. 142</ref>, § 655; amended <ref href="/us/pl/94/546/s1/37">Pub. L. 94–546, § 1(37)</ref>, <date date="1976-10-18">Oct. 18, 1976</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/90/2522">90 Stat. 2522</ref>; renumbered § 943, <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI/s107/b">Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 107(b)</ref>, <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4205">132 Stat. 4205</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id56a63c79-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id56a63c7a-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id56a63c7b-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2018—<ref href="/us/pl/115/282">Pub. L. 115–282</ref> renumbered <ref href="/us/usc/t14/s655">section 655 of this title</ref> as this section.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1976—<ref href="/us/pl/94/546">Pub. L. 94–546</ref> struck out “United States” before “Coast Guard”.</p>
</note>
